Event Description: Harry Potter: Quidditch Championsis a brand-newHarry Pottervideo game based on the fictional sport from the franchise. Quidditch is a Wizarding World sport where contestants fly on brooms and attempt to catch the elusive Golden Snitch. It's featured prominently in theHarry Potterbooks and movies, but it was unfortunately absent from the recently releasedopen worldHarry Potteraction-RPGHogwarts Legacy.

Event Description: Sony capped off its latest PlayStation State of Play event by confirming that a new Astro Bot game will be released on September 6. While the Astro Bot series hasn't been as commercially successful as the platformer mascot games featured on other consoles, the franchise has consistently earned critical acclaim. In fact, the Astro Bot game currently available on PS5 is actually one of the platform's highest-rated games to date.

Marvel vs. Capcom Fighting Collection: Arcade Classics
Event Description: Marvel vs. Capcom Fighting Collection: Arcade Classicsis the latest entry in Capcom'sFighting Collectionseries. With seven games available to play, it's set to revive some of the most classic fighting games of all time. Though it's hard to get one's hopes up after the issues the series has encountered in recent years, it's impossible to ignore that there's suddenly more cause to hold out for a newMarvel vs. Capcomgame.

It’s hard not to compareFunko Fusionto the LEGO games, but that’s not a bad thing. As a fan of TT Games’ work gameifying and LEGO-ifying properties like Harry Potter, Star Wars, and Batman, the idea of a group of former TT Games devs forming 10:10 Games and making Funko Fusion is exciting. And after seeing a brief hands-off preview ofFunko Fusion, that excitement has only grown.

Devolver Digital has once again delivered on very promising upcoming indie games set to release over the next couple of years, one example among them beingThe Plucky Squire. With a trailer opening on a children's storybook with charming, cartoony art, it looked set to be another stylistic indie game fromDevolver Digitalabout a hero named Jot and his adventures across the pages of the book.

Event Description: Capcom has revealed thatDead Rising Deluxe Remaster's release date will be September 18, 2024. Since the announcement thatDead Risingwas getting a remastered version, many fans have been excited at the thought of playing the game with a more modern engine and look. The upcoming title may be able to bring the series back to life.

WhenFrostpunkwas released in 2018, it found a niche aching for new games and capitalized on it in a unique way. City-builders may not be as ubiquitous a genre as the early 2000s, but a survival style of city-builder offered an exciting new take on a classic idea.Frostpunkcaptured that, received impressive reviews, sold over three million copies, and has even been ported to consoles and mobile devices. It should be no surprise then that 11 Bit Studios announced Thursday morning that it was working onFrostpunk 2.

At theMortal Kombat 1Year 2 panel at San Diego Comic-Con, NetherRealm Studios officially announced the upcoming expansion titled Khaos Reigns. This new chapter marks the beginning of Year 2 forMortal Kombat 1and introduces the highly anticipated Kombat Pack 2, which will include a range of new DLC fighters and additional content.

Real Madrid midfielder Jude Bellingham will officially be the featured athlete on the cover ofEA Sports FC 25's Standard Edition, along with being one of the cover stars for the game's Ultimate Edition. At 21 years of age, Bellingham is the youngest star to ever appear on the cover of an EA Sports soccer game, and in addition to gracing the cover ofEA Sports FC 25, he will also serve as the cover athlete forEA Sports FC Mobile.
